  "why": "The paper performs diagnostic analysis on discovered failures by extracting and reporting phoneme-level patterns from the failed test cases (i.e., correlating failures with input structure). This is evidence-based characterization of failure properties (phonemes that are frequently mis-transcribed) derived from the discovered failures themselves. However, the paper does not trace those phoneme-level failure patterns to deeper underlying model vulnerabilities (e.g., corrupted/biased training data, spurious feature reliance, or internal model mechanisms). Therefore it provides partial diagnostic insight but not explanations that link failures to root causes in the model or training data.",
